# Ops fulfillment + pricing data

- **Do not** implement **web scraping** or **scheduled sync jobs** to pull **pricing** from third-party websites. **Reference pricing and catalog rows** come from **admin CSV/XLSX import** (validated, audited) and admin UI. See `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_REFERENCE.md` §2.
- **Fulfillment** is **manual-first**. If any **browser or integration automation** is introduced later, assume it is brittle (layout changes/CAPTCHA/rate limits) and build for failure.
- Every automated path must have:
  - **Per-service enable/disable** and a **kill switch**
  - Job **observability** (status, attempts, timestamps, last error)
  - Artifacts (screenshot/trace) with redaction where needed
  - A **manual fallback** path; admin can mark manual success
- Manual success proof is **tiered by service value/risk** and is **internal-only**.
- **Import jobs** (optional): progress, row errors, audit trail; optional **notify** stakeholders when **reference costs** change after a successful import — **not** “notify on scrape.”

